sec.p:
In this study, the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA) was employed to encode and analyze each preferred term (PT), which was subsequently mapped to the system organ classification (SOC) for further exploration [25]. Firstly, the distribution of SOC features for the 29 ASMs underwent a descriptive analysis. Second, the reporting odds ratio (ROR) [26], proportional reporting ratio (PRR) [27], Bayesian Confidence Propagation Neural Network (BCPNN) [28], and Multi-item Gamma Poisson Shrinker (MGPS) [29] were employed to compute signal values. The utilization of multiple algorithms in combination enables cross-validation to mitigate false positives and enhance the precision of signal detection [30, 31]. The algorithms and criteria are shown in Table 1. The simultaneous fulfillment of four criteria was deemed to be indicative of significant signals.Table 1
